===Usage notes===
*'''Sensible''' describes the reasonable way in which you ''think'' about things or ''do'' things:
*:It wouldn’t be '''sensible''' to start all over again now.

*'''[[Sensitive]]''' describes the emotional way in which you ''react'' to things <He has always been a ''sensitive'' child>:
*:I didn’t realize she was so '''sensitive''' about her work.

